-- Heebner Buys Polaris While Selling Whirlpool, National Oilwell
-- B y   L u   W a n g
-- 2012-08-14T14:31:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-14/heebner-buys-polaris-while-selling-whirlpool-national-oilwell.html
Kenneth Heebner, who ranked as
America’s No. 1 stock picker before losing his touch and most of
his main fund’s assets, bought stakes in  Polaris Industries Inc. (PII) 
during the second quarter while selling Whirlpool Corp.  Capital Growth Management LP purchased 1.44 million shares
of Polaris during the three-month period that ended June 30,
according to a filing with the Securities and Exchange
Commission. The Boston-based money manager bought 735,000 shares
of  Sherwin-Williams Co. (SHW)  and sold out its stakes in Whirlpool and
 National Oilwell Varco Inc. (NOV)   Heebner, whose  CGM Focus Fund (CGMFX)  topped all diversified U.S.
stock mutual funds in the decade through 2007, lost an annual
6.7 percent in the past five years, trailing an average gain of
2 percent by the same group, according to data compiled by
Bloomberg. The fund’s assets plunged to $1.48 billion at the end
of July from the June 2008 peak of $10.3 billion.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Lu Wang  in New York at   lwang8@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
